            "text": "The 3-5-2 formation is football’s version of a Swiss Army knife—flexible, adaptable, and capable of handling just about anything thrown its way. With three at the back, five in midfield, and two up front, it offers a strong balance between defense and control in the middle of the park. The centre-backs form a solid base, while the wing-backs patrol the flanks, offering both defensive cover and attacking width. The midfield trio can dominate the game, keeping possession and dictating play, which makes it difficult for opponents to find a way through. However, if the wing-backs aren’t on their game, the formation can be vulnerable out wide. But when executed properly, the 3-5-2 is a versatile system that can adapt to any opponent, giving you the edge on the pitch.",
